### Schema Layer

#### [NEW] [news_output.py](file:///c:/Users/yassi/OneDrive/Desktop/pfa%20f/schemas/news_output.py)

Pydantic schema defining the Agent 5 output contract. Models include:

- `NewsArticle` — Individual processed article (title, source, sentiment, entities, impact)
- `SentimentResult` — Dual-model sentiment (FinBERT + LLM consensus)
- `EntityExtraction` — Detected financial entities with asset mapping
- `ImpactAssessment` — Multi-factor impact scoring
- `EventDetection` — Black swan / macro event classification
- `TemporalSentiment` — Aggregated sentiment across time windows (1h/24h/7d)
- `MarketSignal` — Final structured signal (bullish/bearish/neutral + confidence)
- `Agent5Output` — Complete output with all sub-models, metadata, execution log

#### [MODIFY] [__init__.py](file:///c:/Users/yassi/OneDrive/Desktop/pfa%20f/schemas/__init__.py)

Export `Agent5Output` and `validate_news_output`.

---

### ML Layer (6 New Modules)

#### [NEW] [news_collector.py](file:///c:/Users/yassi/OneDrive/Desktop/pfa%20f/ml/news_collector.py)

Multi-source news collector with:
- **NewsAPI integration** — Top headlines + everything search for financial keywords
- **RSS feed parser** — feedparser-based collection from Reuters, Bloomberg, CNBC, FT
- **GDELT integration** — Global event database for geopolitical/macro news
- **CryptoPanic integration** — Crypto-specific news aggregation
- **Deduplication** — Title similarity-based dedup before processing
- **Rate limiting** — Per-source rate limiting to respect API quotas
- **Fallback chain** — If primary source fails, try secondaries gracefully
- **Mock mode** — Return pre-built mock articles for testing without API keys

#### [NEW] [news_processor.py](file:///c:/Users/yassi/OneDrive/Desktop/pfa%20f/ml/news_processor.py)

Article processing pipeline:
- **Text cleaning** — Remove HTML, boilerplate, ads, non-English content
- **Relevance filtering** — Score articles by financial keyword density
- **Entity extraction** — spaCy NER + custom financial entity matcher (tickers, asset classes, institutions)
- **Topic classification** — Map articles to topics: `interest_rates`, `inflation`, `crypto`, `earnings`, `geopolitical`, `regulation`, `commodities`
- **Asset mapping** — Map extracted entities to portfolio assets (BTC → crypto, Federal Reserve → bonds, Apple → SPY/tech)

#### [NEW] [sentiment_engine.py](file:///c:/Users/yassi/OneDrive/Desktop/pfa%20f/ml/sentiment_engine.py)

Hybrid sentiment analysis:
- **FinBERT primary** — Financial-domain-specific transformer model (`ProsusAI/finbert`)
- **LLM secondary** — Use existing Gemini/Groq client for deeper contextual sentiment
- **Confidence arbitration** — When FinBERT and LLM disagree, use weighted consensus
- **Numeric conversion** — positive=+1, neutral=0, negative=-1, scaled by confidence
- **Batch processing** — Process multiple articles efficiently
- **Fallback** — If FinBERT unavailable, use LLM-only; if LLM unavailable, use FinBERT-only

#### [NEW] [news_embedding.py](file:///c:/Users/yassi/OneDrive/Desktop/pfa%20f/ml/news_embedding.py)

Vector embedding system:
- **Model**: `sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2` (384-dim, fast, free)
- **Semantic similarity** — Cosine similarity for duplicate/near-duplicate detection
- **Article clustering** — Group related articles about the same event
- **Trend detection** — Track embedding drift over time for emerging narratives
- **Caching** — Cache embeddings to avoid recomputation

#### [NEW] [impact_scorer.py](file:///c:/Users/yassi/OneDrive/Desktop/pfa%20f/ml/impact_scorer.py)

Multi-factor impact scoring:
- **Source weight** — Reuters/Bloomberg=1.0, CNBC/WSJ=0.8, CryptoPanic=0.7, Blogs=0.3
- **Sentiment strength** — abs(sentiment_score) × confidence
- **Topic importance** — `interest_rates`=1.0, `regulation`=0.9, `earnings`=0.7, etc.
- **Temporal recency** — Exponential decay: articles lose 50% impact every 6 hours
- **Entity relevance** — How directly the entity maps to portfolio assets
- **Article clustering boost** — If multiple articles about same event, boost impact
- **Final formula**: `impact = source_w × sentiment_strength × topic_w × recency × entity_relevance × cluster_boost`

#### [NEW] [event_detector.py](file:///c:/Users/yassi/OneDrive/Desktop/pfa%20f/ml/event_detector.py)

Black swan / macro event detection:
- **Pattern matching** — Keyword detection for known event types (Fed meetings, ETF approvals, sanctions, wars, bank failures)
- **Anomaly detection** — Sudden spike in article volume for specific entities
- **Severity classification** — routine, significant, major, critical, black_swan
- **Market impact prediction** — Expected direction and magnitude per asset class
- **Alert generation** — Special flag for events requiring immediate portfolio review

#### [NEW] [temporal_aggregator.py](file:///c:/Users/yassi/OneDrive/Desktop/pfa%20f/ml/temporal_aggregator.py)

Temporal sentiment momentum:
- **Time windows** — 1 hour, 24 hours, 7 days
- **Exponentially weighted** — Recent articles weighted more heavily
- **Per-asset-class sentiment** — Separate trends for crypto, equities, bonds, commodities
- **Momentum signals** — Direction: accelerating, stable, decelerating
- **Regime sentiment** — Overall market sentiment regime (very_bearish → very_bullish)

